###Global

According to Sina's real-time statistics, as of March 16,87,448 cases of overseas new crown pneumonia (NCP) had been confirmed, 3,288 cases had died and 9,212 cases had been cured except in China (including Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan) .

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Note: The new 0 indicates that no data have been announced yet on the same day. Source: Sina

0849[ more than 85,000 cases of newly diagnosed pneumonia outside China ]

According to the latest real time statistics from the Johns Hopkins University, as of 08:33 on the 16th Beijing time, there were more than 160,000 confirmed cases of new pneumonia worldwide, and the total number of confirmed cases outside China exceeded 85,000, 86,435 cases. Italy and Iran have more than 10,000 cases.

0800[ who: 72,469 confirmed cases of new coronary pneumonia outside China ]

As of 10:00 Central European time on the 15th (17:00 China Standard Time on the 15th) , the number of confirmed cases of new pneumonia outside China had increased by 10,955 from the previous day to 72,469, according to World Health Organization's Daily outbreak report The number of deaths outside China increased by 333 from the previous day to 2,531.

Globally, 10,982 new cases of pneumonia were confirmed, bringing the total to 153517, and 343 deaths, bringing the total to 5,735.

0800[ EU begins partial restriction on export of Protective Medical Supplies ]

On March 15, the European Union announced that in order to ensure the supply of defensive medical materials within the European Union, the export of such materials must be authorized by the relevant countries. Personal protective medical supplies include face masks, face masks and protective helmets.

###The United States

0800[ more than 3,200 confirmed cases ]

At least 3,244 new cases of pneumonia, including 62 deaths, had been confirmed in the United States by the afternoon of May 15, according to real-time statistics released by the Johns Hopkins University.

On the 15th, many local governments in the United States upgraded the epidemic prevention and control measures, to restaurants, bars and other places to introduce restrictions on business. The mayor of Boston has ordered all bars and restaurants to reduce their capacity by 50 percent and close by 11 p.m. . Any violation will result in a 30-day suspension. Ohio requires all bars and restaurants to be closed by 9 p.m. The Governor of California has ordered all bars, nightclubs and other places in the state to be closed, and restaurants to be cut in half.

0800[ the Federal Reserve cuts interest rates to near zero and will restart quantitative easing ]

On Sunday afternoon, the Federal Reserve abruptly cut the federal funds rate band by 1 percentage point to 0%-0.25% and extended the maturity of loans to 90 days. The Fed also cut the reserve requirement ratio for thousands of banks to zero.

The Fed said it would start quantitative easing on Monday, buying at least $500bn of treasury bonds and $200bn of mortgage-backed securities over the next few months to help keep the market functioning.

0800. Clinical trials of a new coronavirus vaccine begin Monday

###Italy

0800(24747 confirmed cases of new coronary pneumonia, 1809 deaths)

There were 3590 new cases and 368 new deaths, with a cumulative death of 1809. There were 1672 severe cases and 2335 patients were cured.

###France

0800[ increase in confirmed cases to 5400 deaths to 120]

The number of confirmed cases was 900 more than the previous day, of which 400 were in serious condition.

###Germany

0800[4,838 confirmed cases, 1043 new cases ]

As of 15:00 local time on March 15, Germany had confirmed 4,838 cases of new coronavirus pneumonia, including 12 deaths, according to the latest data released by the Robert Koch. Compared with 15:00 on March 14th, 1043 new cases and 4 new deaths were recorded.

Germany will be 16 from 8:00 am local time, the temporary closure with France, Austria, Luxembourg, Switzerland, Denmark 5 borders. However, in contrast to the strict closure of the border, there are no restrictions on cargo vehicles and on workers travelling to and from the border with permits, and German citizens can enter the country in principle at any time.

###Iran

0800[ Iran's national mobilization program has completed screening of 10 million people ]

Of these, 210,000 developed symptoms such as headache and fever. Of these 210,000,30,000 were sent to medical centres due to severe symptoms, of which 1,200 were transferred to hospitals and 900 were hospitalized.

Recently, Iran launched a national mobilization plan, according to which 300,000 outbreak investigation teams will start from the areas affected by the epidemic, and will ask people one by one based on their personal information. Suspected infected people will go to medical institutions for testing, those who test positive will be quarantined at home and will receive medication and instructions.

[ official: First Vice President Jahangiri has returned to work without new crown pneumonia ]

Jahangiri has tested negative for the new coronavirus, Iranian state television reported Monday.

On the 11th of this month, Iran's Fars News Agency reported that First Vice President Jahangiri was infected with the new coronavirus.

###United Kingdom

0800[232 newly diagnosed cases of coronary pneumonia, 1372 confirmed cases ]

According to the Department of Social Security, from 9:00 a.m. on March 14 to 9:00 a.m. on March 15, there were 232 new confirmed cases of pneumonia in the UK, bringing the total to 1,372; 14 new deaths and 35 cumulative deaths.

###Sweden

0800[ confirmed 992 cases of new coronary pneumonia ]

Local time, the Swedish Public Health Bureau announced that as of 14:00 on the 15th, Sweden has a cumulative total of 992 cases of new pneumonia, two deaths. It was added that the number of confirmed and suspected cases was changing and that there were some delays in reporting new cases and additional data. This figure represents only the confirmed cases, not the total number of infected persons.

###Japan

0800[ Diamond Princess Quarantine ends with 712 confirmed cases ]

The last group of people to leave the ship for 14 days of Health Observation ended on the 15th, and quarantine work was completed, the Jiji Press reported Monday. Of the 15 newly diagnosed cases, 6 were Japanese and 9 were of other nationalities, mainly including those who had been taken to hospital due to acute illness and accompanying nursing staff.

###Canada

0800(313 cases of newly diagnosed Canadian pneumonia covering all 10 provinces)

###Norway

0800[ violation of municipal and national prohibition of epidemic prevention is punishable by up to four years'imprisonment ]

Local time March 15, Norwegian radio and television (NRK) reported that as of 20:00 on the 15th, Norway's cumulative confirmed cases of 1234 cases, 3 deaths.

Norway's Prime Minister, Solberg, said the government would provide 100 billion Norwegian kroner (72 billion yuan) to the business sector as part of a capital guarantee program aimed at ensuring liquidity in the business sector during the outbreak of new pneumonia.

###Austria

0800[ increase in confirmed cases to 860, about to implement the most stringent controls in history ]

As of 15:00 local time on March 15,8,167 new coronavirus tests had been carried out in Austria, with 860 confirmed cases and two deaths, according to the website of the Austrian Ministry of Health and Austrian media.

To contain the outbreak, the Austrian government has stepped up prevention and control measures by cancelling all public gatherings and closing public places such as stadium and children's play areas. Only individuals or co-residents are allowed to go out together, and violators are liable to heavy fines.

###Serbia

0800[ declaring a state of emergency in hopes of technical and material assistance from China ]

Local time from the evening of 15, Serbia will take close the border, classes, banned more than 50 people gathering measures. From the 16th, the hospital where the new pneumonia was diagnosed will be under military supervision, the police will supervise the quarantine measures, and any violation of the regulations will be sentenced to three years in prison.

'when the going gets tough, we can't count on the EU, ' President of Serbia Vuczicj said in a televised speech. 'The only person who will help Serbia is China. '.

As of 18:00 on the 15th, 48 cases had been confirmed in the country, of which 2 were in critical condition.

###Turkey

0800[ Turkey announces evacuation policy from nine European countries ]

Turkish Vice President Oktay said there would be no flights from Germany, Spain, France, Austria, Norway, Denmark, Sweden, Belgium and the Netherlands from 2400 hours local time on March 15. Turkish citizens travelling for short periods in the above-mentioned countries, or Turkish students studying in these countries, who wish to return to their country, are required to submit their applications to the Turkish Diplomatic Agency of the host country before 16 March. Turkey will have until March 17 to take back citizens who have applied to return home.
In the early hours of March 16 local time, Turkey's health minister, Koca, said 12 new cases of pneumonia were confirmed in Turkey, bringing the total to 18.

###Latin America

0800[79 new confirmed cases of pneumonia in Brazil, bringing the total to 200]

São Paulo has 136 confirmed cases, or 68% of the country's total.

0830[ first confirmed case in Bahamas, patient has no recent foreign travel history ]

The patient, a 61 year old Bahamian woman, was admitted Monday with respiratory system symptoms. She was diagnosed in the early morning of the 15th and had no recent travel history.

0800[ five people aboard a British cruise ship have been diagnosed with new pneumonia after it ran aground off the Bahamas ]

A cruise ship carrying 600 Britons is stranded off the Bahamas, according to British Sky News. Five people on board have been diagnosed with new crown pneumonia and 20 passengers, including a doctor, and 20 crew members are being quarantined.

The Bahamas has refused to allow the cruise ship, which is owned by a British company, to dock and has asked it to go to another island for food, fuel and medicine.

###Africa

[26 countries in Africa report confirmed cases, bringing the total to 280] according to data posted on social media on the evening of March 15 by Ahmad, deputy director of the African Center for Disease Control and Prevention, the number of countries on the African continent reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 rose to 26, bringing the total to 280. In the past 24 hours, Seychelles, Equatorial Guinea, Congo (Brazzaville) , the Central African Republic and other countries have reported their first confirmed cases.

0800[ South Africa is in a state of national disaster ]

On the evening of March 15, South Africa's president, Ramaphosa, declared a state of national disaster. Restrictions on South African nationals travelling to high-risk countries and visa cancellation for some high-risk countries and regions. As of Monday, 35 of the 53 land crossings will be closed, barring government agencies from all unnecessary travel.
